# {{ product_name }} Charts Skill

This skill enables you to render interactive charts in any {{ product_name }} chat
surface: board chat, group chat, channel threads, and planning chat.

There are **two methods** for posting charts. Use the **structured method** (Method A)
whenever possible — it is more reliable, validated server-side, and works on every
surface. The legacy fenced-block method (Method B) still works as a fallback.

---

## Supported chart types

| `type`   | Description                                                |
|----------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| `line`   | Line chart — burndowns, trends, cumulative flow            |
| `area`   | Area (filled) chart — velocity, throughput over time       |
| `bar`    | Bar chart — workload by agent, task counts, comparisons    |
| `pie`    | Pie chart — status breakdown, priority split               |
| `donut`  | Donut chart — same as pie, with a centred value label      |

---

## Chart spec reference

```json
{
  "type":   "<line|area|bar|pie|donut>",
  "title":  "<optional heading shown above chart>",
  "xKey":   "<field name used as X axis or pie label>",
  "yKeys":  "<field name, or array of field names, for Y values>",
  "xLabel": "<optional X axis label>",
  "yLabel": "<optional Y axis label>",
  "data":   [ { "<xKey>": "...", "<yKey>": 0 } ],
  "colors": ["<optional hex or CSS colour overrides, one per series>"],
  "height": 260
}
```

**Required fields**: `type`, `xKey`, `yKeys`, `data`.

All values mapped by `yKeys` **must be numbers**. The `xKey` dimension is the
category/label (string or number both fine).

---

## Method A — Structured chart result (preferred)

Post with `content_type: "mcp_app_result"` and `metadata.app: "chart"`. The UI
renders the chart automatically without requiring a fenced-block inside the message.

**Required metadata shape**:
```json
{
  "app": "chart",
  "spec": { <chart spec — see above> }
}
```

### Board chat
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/memory" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "content": "Sprint burndown for current sprint.",
    "tags": ["chat"],
    "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
    "app_metadata": {
      "app": "chart",
      "spec": {
        "type": "line",
        "title": "Sprint Burndown",
        "xKey": "day",
        "yKeys": ["remaining", "ideal"],
        "data": [
          {"day": "Mon", "remaining": 24, "ideal": 20},
          {"day": "Fri", "remaining":  4, "ideal":  4}
        ]
      }
    }
  }'
```

### Group chat (via board context)
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/group-memory" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "content": "Team velocity this quarter.",
    "tags": ["chat"],
    "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
    "app_metadata": {
      "app": "chart",
      "spec": {
        "type": "bar",
        "title": "Open Tasks per Agent",
        "xKey": "agent",
        "yKeys": ["tasks"],
        "data": [
          {"agent": "Alice", "tasks": 4},
          {"agent": "Bob",   "tasks": 7}
        ]
      }
    }
  }'
```

### Channel thread
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/threads/{thread_id}/messages" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "content": "Deployment timeline.",
    "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
    "event_metadata": {
      "app": "chart",
      "spec": {
        "type": "area",
        "title": "Sprint Velocity",
        "xKey": "sprint",
        "yKeys": ["completed", "committed"],
        "data": [
          {"sprint": "S1", "completed": 900,  "committed": 1200},
          {"sprint": "S2", "completed": 1320, "committed": 1320}
        ]
      }
    }
  }'
```

### Planning agent reply
When calling the plan agent-update endpoint, set `content_type` and `app_metadata`
alongside `reply`:
```json
{
  "reply": "Here is the burndown chart for the sprint.",
  "content_type": "mcp_app_result",
  "app_metadata": {
    "app": "chart",
    "spec": {
      "type": "line",
      "title": "Sprint Burndown",
      "xKey": "day",
      "yKeys": ["remaining"],
      "data": [{"day": "Mon", "remaining": 24}]
    }
  }
}
```

