## Data sources

Always query the {{ product_name }} API to collect real data before composing a
chart. Useful endpoints:

| Data needed | API path |
|---|---|
| Task list with statuses | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/tasks` |
| Sprint list | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/sprints` |
| Sprint tickets and estimates | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/sprints/{sprint_id}/tickets` |
| Board activity events | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/activity` |
| Velocity & estimation accuracy | `GET /api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/velocity` |

For velocity charts, use `estimate_minutes` and `actual_minutes` from sprint tickets or the velocity
endpoint. Aggregate and convert to hours for display (divide by 60).
Use `jq` to aggregate counts from the task list before building your `data` array.

---

## Rules

- **Never fabricate data.** Always query the API and aggregate before charting.
- **Numbers only** for Y-axis values. Strings cause the chart to fall back gracefully.
- **Limit `data` to ≤ 500 rows.** Aggregate/summarise larger datasets first.
- Use **Method A** (structured) as the primary approach. Use **Method B** (fenced block)
  only as a fallback when the endpoint does not yet support `content_type`.
- The backend validates `metadata` for `mcp_app_result` — it will return 422 if
  `metadata.app` is missing or not a string.

